%description:
TCP AccECN (Workstream G) G9.1: fallback-matrix completeness --
tcpEcnMode="accecn-passive" as the LISTENER (passive-open) role. Server
is accecn-passive (willing to ACCEPT AccECN if a peer requests it, but
never initiates it itself); client is accecn (active opener, sends the
real SEWA request). Confirms the asymmetry TCP_ECN_MODE_ACCECN_PASSIVE
is meant to express: processSynInListen()'s AccECN-accept check
(TcpConnectionRcvSegment.cc) already treats ACCECN and ACCECN_PASSIVE
identically for the PASSIVE-accept role (both listed in that check's
`||`), so this scenario negotiates real AccECN exactly like
tcp_accecn_negotiate_accepted_1.test's both-accecn scenario does -- this
test's job is to pin that accecn-passive on the listener specifically
(not just accecn) reaches the same outcome, and the companion
tcp_accecn_fallback_2.test pins the other half (accecn-passive on the
ACTIVE opener never even offers to negotiate).

Falsification: none needed as a separate run -- the assertion itself
(AccECN successfully negotiated with the server configured
accecn-passive, not accecn) is the falsification of "passive means
inert/no-op", the plausible-but-wrong reading of the mode name.

%inifile: omnetpp.ini
[General]
record-vector-results = false
ned-path = .;../../../../src;../../lib

network = inet.test.moduletest.lib.TcpTestNet1

cmdenv-event-banners=false
cmdenv-express-mode=false
cmdenv-log-prefix="[%c]: "

*.testing=false
*.tcptester.script=""

*.cli_app.localAddress="10.0.0.1"
*.cli_app.localPort=1000
*.cli_app.connectAddress="10.0.0.2"
*.cli_app.connectPort=2000
*.cli_app.active=true
*.cli_app.tOpen=0s
*.cli_app.tSend=-1s
*.cli_app.sendBytes=0B
*.cli_app.tClose=-1s
*.cli_app.sendScript=""

*.srv_app.localAddress="10.0.0.2"
*.srv_app.localPort=2000
*.srv_app.connectAddress="10.0.0.1"
*.srv_app.connectPort=1000
*.srv_app.active=false
*.srv_app.tOpen=0s
*.srv_app.tSend=-1s
*.srv_app.sendBytes=0B
*.srv_app.tClose=-1s
*.srv_app.sendScript=""

*.*_tcp.sackSupport = false
*.*_tcp.windowScalingSupport = false
*.*_tcp.timestampSupport = false
*.*_tcp.mss = 1000
*.*_tcp.tcpAlgorithmClass = "TcpReno"

*.cli_tcp.tcpEcnMode = "accecn"
*.srv_tcp.tcpEcnMode = "accecn-passive"

include ../../lib/tcp-legacy.ini

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%file: postrun.pl
open FILE, '<test.out';
while($sor = <FILE>)
{
    if ($sor =~ /^\[testing\]: (.*)$/)
    {
        print "$1\n";
    }
}
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command:  perl ./postrun.pl
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Client's SYN: SEWA, requesting AccECN as usual.
%contains: postrun-command(1).out
[0.001 A001] A.1000 > B.2000: S E W N 0:0(0) win 7504   Option(s): MaxSegSize
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Server's SYN-ACK: SW. -- accecn-passive still accepts a peer-initiated AccECN request.
%contains: postrun-command(1).out
[0.003 B001] A.1000 < B.2000: A S W 500:500(0) ack 1 win 7504   Option(s): MaxSegSize
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%contains: stdout
AccECN-setup SYN-ACK sent... AccECN is enabled
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%contains: stdout
AccECN-setup SYN-ACK received... AccECN is enabled.
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
